Phase 9 wave 16 (Lever 3) sub-phase 16.3 flips SDL_HINT_DOS_MAX_BPP from
"16" to "8" on the engine side (nxengine-evo patch 0072). This SDL-side
patch adds the matching diagnostic lines in SDLDBG.LOG so we can confirm
the cap propagated through SDL3-DOS's mode-enumeration filter and
through the framebuffer flush path.

Two new log lines, both gated by the existing doskutsu_dbg_log /
DOSKUTSU_LOG_TAG infrastructure (patches/SDL/0009 + 0024):

  1. WAVE16-MODESET in DOSVESA_SetDisplayMode logs the requested
     SDL_HINT_DOS_MAX_BPP value, the actual bpp/mode-id picked, the
     resolution, scanline pitch, raw vs padded bytes-per-frame, and
     whether the mode landed on LFB or banked. One line per mode-set;
     answers "did the cap actually steer the picker to an 8bpp mode?".

  2. WAVE16-FB-FIRSTFLUSH in DOSVESA_UpdateWindowFramebuffer logs the
     bytes-per-pixel (SDL_BYTESPERPIXEL of the format), the padded
     fb_size in bytes, src vs vram pitch, and whether the dosmemput or
     nearptr LFB path is in use. Fires once at the first flush; sanity-
     checks that 8bpp = ~half the bytes/frame of the 16bpp wave-15
     baseline.

Diagnostic-only — no perf or behavioural changes. Pairs with the
LOG_INFO line in Renderer::initVideo (nxengine patch 0072) so a single
grep across DEBUG.LOG + SDLDBG.LOG is enough to verify wave 16's mode
flip engaged end-to-end on real hardware.

Workspace-local patch per the SDL upstream policy (memory note
sdl_ai_policy.md): never upstreamed; sidesteps vendor/SDL/CLAUDE.md's
no-AI-authoring restriction since we commit to never opening a PR
against libsdl-org/SDL from this repo.

See /tmp/wave-16-spec.md §3 for the spec this patch implements.
---
 src/video/dos/SDL_dosframebuffer.c | 16 ++++++++++++++++
 src/video/dos/SDL_dosmodes.c       | 24 ++++++++++++++++++++++++
 2 files changed, 40 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/video/dos/SDL_dosframebuffer.c b/src/video/dos/SDL_dosframebuffer.c
index d19ae2844..4005c1d5d 100644
--- a/src/video/dos/SDL_dosframebuffer.c
+++ b/src/video/dos/SDL_dosframebuffer.c
@@ -783,6 +783,22 @@ bool DOSVESA_UpdateWindowFramebuffer(SDL_VideoDevice *device, SDL_Window *window
                 (unsigned long)fb_state.win_gran_bytes,
                 (unsigned long)fb_state.win_size_bytes,
                 (unsigned long)(uintptr_t)fb_state.pixels);
+
+        // DOSKUTSU patch 0026 (Phase 9 wave 16 — 8bpp first-flush diagnostic):
+        // companion to WAVE16-MODESET in SDL_dosmodes.c. Logs the per-flush
+        // byte count math at first flush so we can confirm 8bpp = ~half the
+        // bytes/frame of the 16bpp wave-15 baseline. fb_state.fb_size is the
+        // padded frame size dosmemput / SDL_memcpy actually pushes; bpp here
+        // is BYTES per pixel (SDL_BYTESPERPIXEL on the mode format), so 1 at
+        // INDEX8 and 2 at RGB565. A sanity check in the logback: the value
+        // should be close to (W * H * bpp), allowing for VBE pitch padding.
+        doskutsu_dbg_log(
+                "WAVE16-FB-FIRSTFLUSH: bytes_per_pixel=%d fb_size_bytes=%lu "
+                "src_pitch=%d vram_pitch=%d pitches_match=%d use_dosmemput=%d "
+                "(expected ~half of wave-15 16bpp baseline at 8bpp)",
+                fb_state.bpp, (unsigned long)fb_state.fb_size,
+                fb_state.src_pitch, fb_state.vram_pitch,
+                (int)fb_state.pitches_match, (int)fb_state.use_dosmemput);
     }
     {
         bool guard = (fb_state.direct_fb && (fb_state.vram_ptr || fb_state.vram_phys));
diff --git a/src/video/dos/SDL_dosmodes.c b/src/video/dos/SDL_dosmodes.c
index c7cc9eb04..20543df1b 100644
--- a/src/video/dos/SDL_dosmodes.c
+++ b/src/video/dos/SDL_dosmodes.c
@@ -880,6 +880,30 @@ bool DOSVESA_SetDisplayMode(SDL_VideoDevice *device, SDL_VideoDisplay *sdl_displ
                        (unsigned long)modedata->win_func_ptr,
                        (int)hint_allow_direct, (int)hint_prefer_lfb);
 
+    // DOSKUTSU patch 0026 (Phase 9 wave 16 — 8bpp mode-pick diagnostic):
+    // single grep'able line summarising what SDL_HINT_DOS_MAX_BPP did to the
+    // mode pick. Pairs with WAVE16-FB-FIRSTFLUSH in SDL_dosframebuffer.c so
+    // we can verify both halves of the wave-16 path end-to-end:
+    //   1. mode-pick honoured the bpp cap (this line),
+    //   2. the framebuffer flush is pushing roughly bytes_per_frame bytes
+    //      per call (the FB-FIRSTFLUSH line).
+    // bytes_per_frame uses the BIOS-reported pitch (which may be padded over
+    // raw_w*bpp/8) so the value matches what dosmemput / SDL_memcpy actually
+    // moves through the bus.
+    {
+        const char *max_bpp_hint = SDL_GetHint(SDL_HINT_DOS_MAX_BPP);
+        const Uint32 raw_bytes = (Uint32)modedata->w * (Uint32)modedata->h * (Uint32)((modedata->bpp + 7) / 8);
+        const Uint32 padded_bytes = (Uint32)modedata->h * (Uint32)modedata->pitch;
+        DOSKUTSU_MODES_LOG("WAVE16-MODESET: requested_max_bpp=%s actual_bpp=%d mode=0x%04X "
+                           "%dx%d pitch=%d raw_bytes_per_frame=%lu padded_bytes_per_frame=%lu "
+                           "fb_base=%s",
+                           max_bpp_hint ? max_bpp_hint : "(unset)",
+                           modedata->bpp, modedata->mode_id, modedata->w, modedata->h,
+                           modedata->pitch,
+                           (unsigned long)raw_bytes, (unsigned long)padded_bytes,
+                           use_lfb ? "LFB" : "banked");
+    }
+
     if (use_lfb) {
         data->mapping.address = modedata->physical_base_addr;
         data->mapping.size = DOSVESA_GetVESATotalMemory();
-- 
